TextBody:
Hi Vaneet,

The destination details is a seperate column.  You will need to click on the "Show/Hide Columns" and then select "Destination Details".  Please also note that this column will only be visible if you have "Reporting V2" enabled under "System Configuration" > "System Settings".


You will also need to have "Deep Packet Inspection" enabled if you would like the URLs or Domains to be reported.  Deep Packet Inspection can be enabled under "Device Control" > "Global Settings".

I have made a short video recording showing how to enable Report V2 and how to select the "Destination Details" column and where you will see the destination URLs.  Please see the attached video recording "Enable Report V2 and Destination Details.mkv"



Kind regards

For the details listed under the "Destination" tab, these are the applications that were used as an exit point when the reported data / files were transmitted.  For example you will see that the names under this tab corresponds to the names of the apps selected under "Policy Exit Points" in the Content Aware Policy.



I hope this information helps, if you have any follow up questions then please do let us know.

TextBody:
Hi Vaneet,

If you do not want to have internal domains restricted then you will need to remove them from the DPI denylists under "Denylists and Allowlists" > "Denylists" > "Domain and URL", select the relevant dictionary and edit it to remove the internal domains.  Click on save and then update the policies on the endpoint machines.  As an example please see the short video recording attached "How to remove URL and Domains from DPI Denylits.mkv" that demonstrates how to do this.

Hi Vaneet,

The destination details is a seperate column.  You will need to click on the "Show/Hide Columns" and then select "Destination Details".  Please also note that this column will only be visible if you have "Reporting V2" enabled under "System Configuration" > "System Settings".


You will also need to have "Deep Packet Inspection" enabled if you would like the URLs or Domains to be reported.  Deep Packet Inspection can be enabled under "Device Control" > "Global Settings".

I have made a short video recording showing how to enable Report V2 and how to select the "Destination Details" column and where you will see the destination URLs.  Please see the attached video recording "Enable Report V2 and Destination Details.mkv"

Hi Vaneet,

The destination details is a seperate column.  You will need to click on the "Show/Hide Columns" and then select "Destination Details".  Please also note that this column will only be visible if you have "Reporting V2" enabled under "System Configuration" > "System Settings".

I have made a short video recording showing how to enable Report V2 and how to select the "Destination Details" column and where you will see the destination URLs.  Please see the attached video recording "Enable Report V2 and Destination Details.mkv"

Hi Vaneet,

The destination details is a seperate column.  You will need to click on the "Show/Hide Columns" and then select "Destination Details".  Please also note that this column will only be visible if you have "Reporting V2" enabled under "System Configuration" > "System Settings".


You will also need to have "Deep Packet Inspection" enabled if you would like the URLs or Domains to be reported.  Deep Packet Inspection can be enabled under "Device Control" > "Global Settings".

I have made a short video recording showing how to enable Report V2 and how to select the "Destination Details" column and where you will see the destination URLs.  Please see the attached video recording "Enable Report V2 and Destination Details.mkv"



Kind regards

If you do not want to have internal domains restricted then you will need to remove them from the DPI denylists under "Denylists and Allowlists" > "Denylists" > "Domain and URL", select the relevant dictionary and edit it to remove the internal domains.  Click on save and then update the policies on the endpoint machines.  As an example please see the short video recording attached "How to remove URL and Domains from DPI Denylits.mkv" that demonstrates how to do this.

Subject: RE: Netwrix Support Ticket #426466 - - No visibility of captured incident destination URL [ ref:!00D70091pB.!500Qk0I2XQX:ref ]



 

Hi Vaneet,

The destination details is a seperate column.  You will need to click on the "Show/Hide Columns" and then select "Destination Details".  Please also note that this column will only be visible if you have "Reporting V2" enabled under "System Configuration" > "System Settings".


You will also need to have "Deep Packet Inspection" enabled if you would like the URLs or Domains to be reported.  Deep Packet Inspection can be enabled under "Device Control" > "Global Settings".

I have made a short video recording showing how to enable Report V2 and how to select the "Destination Details" column and where you will see the destination URLs.  Please see the attached video recording "Enable Report V2 and Destination Details.mkv"



Kind regards

Hi Vaneet,

The destination details is a seperate column.  You will need to click on the "Show/Hide Columns" and then select "Destination Details".  Please also note that this column will only be visible if you have "Reporting V2" enabled under "System Configuration" > "System Settings".


You will also need to have "Deep Packet Inspection" enabled if you would like the URLs or Domains to be reported.  Deep Packet Inspection can be enabled under "Device Control" > "Global Settings".

I have made a short video recording showing how to enable Report V2 and how to select the "Destination Details" column and where you will see the destination URLs.  Please see the attached video recording "Enable Report V2 and Destination Details.mkv"



Kind regards

Would you like us to proceed to create with this build of EPP client ?

Hi Vaneet,

The destination details is a seperate column.  You will need to click on the "Show/Hide Columns" and then select "Destination Details".  Please also note that this column will only be visible if you have "Reporting V2" enabled under "System Configuration" > "System Settings".


You will also need to have "Deep Packet Inspection" enabled if you would like the URLs or Domains to be reported.  Deep Packet Inspection can be enabled under "Device Control" > "Global Settings".

I have made a short video recording showing how to enable Report V2 and how to select the "Destination Details" column and where you will see the destination URLs.  Please see the attached video recording "Enable Report V2 and Destination Details.mkv"

Subject: RE: Netwrix Support Ticket #426466 - - No visibility of captured incident destination URL [ ref:!00D70091pB.!500Qk0I2XQX:ref ]

Hi Vaneet,

The destination details is a seperate column.  You will need to click on the "Show/Hide Columns" and then select "Destination Details".  Please also note that this column will only be visible if you have "Reporting V2" enabled under "System Configuration" > "System Settings".


You will also need to have "Deep Packet Inspection" enabled if you would like the URLs or Domains to be reported.  Deep Packet Inspection can be enabled under "Device Control" > "Global Settings".

I have made a short video recording showing how to enable Report V2 and how to select the "Destination Details" column and where you will see the destination URLs.  Please see the attached video recording "Enable Report V2 and Destination Details.mkv"



Kind regards

Hi Vaneet,

The destination details is a seperate column.  You will need to click on the "Show/Hide Columns" and then select "Destination Details".  Please also note that this column will only be visible if you have "Reporting V2" enabled under "System Configuration" > "System Settings".


You will also need to have "Deep Packet Inspection" enabled if you would like the URLs or Domains to be reported.  Deep Packet Inspection can be enabled under "Device Control" > "Global Settings".

I have made a short video recording showing how to enable Report V2 and how to select the "Destination Details" column and where you will see the destination URLs.  Please see the attached video recording "Enable Report V2 and Destination Details.mkv"

Hi Vaneet,

The destination details is a seperate column.  You will need to click on the "Show/Hide Columns" and then select "Destination Details".  Please also note that this column will only be visible if you have "Reporting V2" enabled under "System Configuration" > "System Settings".


You will also need to have "Deep Packet Inspection" enabled if you would like the URLs or Domains to be reported.  Deep Packet Inspection can be enabled under "Device Control" > "Global Settings".

I have made a short video recording showing how to enable Report V2 and how to select the "Destination Details" column and where you will see the destination URLs.  Please see the attached video recording "Enable Report V2 and Destination Details.mkv"



Kind regards

Hello Vaneet,

Thank you for your email and update.

Can I ask you to have a look at DPI configurations and send us a screenshot of the current settings please? You will find it under "Device Control" > "Global Settings" > "DPI Configuration" or you can check under "Computers" for computer level.

If  "DPI Bypass" is currently turned off, can you switch this setting on, save the settings, update the policies on the affected endpoint computers then test to see if the issue still persists please?




Please let us know the result of the above.




Kind regards

Hi Vaneet,

The destination details is a seperate column.  You will need to click on the "Show/Hide Columns" and then select "Destination Details".  Please also note that this column will only be visible if you have "Reporting V2" enabled under "System Configuration" > "System Settings".


You will also need to have "Deep Packet Inspection" enabled if you would like the URLs or Domains to be reported.  Deep Packet Inspection can be enabled under "Device Control" > "Global Settings".

I have made a short video recording showing how to enable Report V2 and how to select the "Destination Details" column and where you will see the destination URLs.  Please see the attached video recording "Enable Report V2 and Destination Details.mkv"
